  <discussion>Species 7 (4 in the flora):</discussion>
  <discussion>A. Cronquist and D. D. Keck (1957) correctly grouped the then known members of sect.
        Blepharodon under their Machaeranthera series Originales (an illegitimate name). These taxa
        had been treated in Haplopappus sect. Blepharodon by H. M. Hall (1928). Included as well
        were: H. arenarius Bentham (Mexico), H. junceus, H. spinulosus, and H. stenolobus Greene
        (Mexico) (here treated in Xanthisma sect. Sideranthus); H. phyllocephalus and H. aureus (now
        members of 204. Rayjacksonia); and H. brickellioides (now a member of 206.
        Hazardia).</discussion>
